  "slug": "fantastic-fish-pie",
  "title": "Fantastic Fish Pie",
  "subtitle": "Cod, hard-boiled eggs, and wilted spinach in a cream sauce, topped with mashed potato",
  "excerpt": "A proper British fish pie with cod, quartered hard-boiled eggs, and squeezed spinach in a cream, cheese, and mustard sauce, topped with mashed potato and baked until golden. Serves four. From Rebecca's kitchen.",
  "type": "RECIPE",
  "sourceNotes": "From Rebecca's personal cookbook, a recipe she's made many times in her own kitchen.",
  "body": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A fish pie that comes together with one pan and one baking dish. The cream sauce is made from the onion and carrot softened in a little oil, then double cream brought to the boil with grated cheddar, lemon juice, mustard, and parsley stirred in off the heat. The raw fish goes in uncooked; it finishes in the oven alongside the eggs and spinach."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Squeeze the spinach well before adding so it doesn't water down the sauce. The potato topping doesn't need to look tidy; a rough surface browns more and gives better texture."
          }
        ]
      },
